column54:
when ActionResponse.setParameter() is set then during the same request after going into render phase RenderRequest.getParameter will provide parameter with broken encoding.

So if you have code like:

public void processAction(ActionRequest req, ActionResponse resp) throws PortletException, PortletSecurityException, IOException
   {
      resp.setRenderParameter("text",req.getParameter("text"));
   }      

   protected void doView(RenderRequest req, RenderResponse resp) throws PortletException, PortletSecurityException, IOException
   {
      String param = req.getParameter("text");
   .......
  .....
   }

Then:
1) If you submit form directly into Render, params in doView() will be retrieved correctly
2) If you submit form into Action, params in processAction() will be retrieved correctly, then set in resp.setParameter() and after going into doView() they will be retrieved with broken encoding.

