21/Jul/05 9:25 PM;dougmaceachern;Notice for the Args the operator is 'Peq', rather than 'eq'.  'P' flag means parent process id.  More than 1 process will match State.Name.eq=Apache, but only one will have its parent's args == -k runservice
Similar is used in the unix query, there could be a few dozen that match State.Name.eq=httpd.  Each child process will have parent Name == httpd, only the top-level parent will have a Name other than httpd.

We use BCEL to generate the code, windows query turns into:

