We came across a ClassCastException when a Fqn is constructed using any object but java.lang.String and calling getName() on this Fqn.

After inspection of the code, we saw that the method getName() does a direct cast to java.lang.String when the Fqn is not the root. However, this is in contradiction with the constructors of the class Fqn (which tells us, you can use any object to create an Fqn). Or are you supposed to use Strings for the construction of Fqns?

We resolved this problem by changing the following line (#296) in Fqn.java (CVS version 1.3.0.SP1):

else return (String) elements.get(elements.size() - 1);
to
else return String.valueof(elements.get(elements.size() - 1));

And the test for verifycation:
