===============
Short Story:
================
Scott made a change to SecurityAssociation wherein on the pop of a SubjectContext from the stack, the legacy threadlocal variable "threadPrincipal" would be updated with the principal that exists in the stack. The change to SecurityAssociation class is revision:1.19.2.12 with the cvs message:
"When popping the subject context update the legacy single-valued principal/credential with the next stack values. Add a peekSubjectContext that requires a RuntimePermission("org.jboss.security.SecurityAssociation.getPrincipalInfo"). "

This is creating an issue when running with the jacc config and under a securitymanager which is described as follows:
The testcase does an update on the entitybean method and in a finally block, does a logout on the logincontext. This pops up the SubjectContext and thereby setting the principal on the SA to be "jduke" when infact the entitybean invocation happened with a principal "audituser2". 

The reason for this anomaly is that the after the method completes, the TxManager does a callback to the entitysynchronizationinterceptor and the CMP audit logic uses the latest principal set on the SA (which due to the login.logout) got set to the previous principal on the stack.

=============
The long story:
==============

This seems to be busted in the following block of code:

org.jboss.ejb.EnterpriseContext.java
============================
/**
       * The implementation of getCallerPrincipal()
