03/Jun/10 4:48 AM;sergiykarpenko;Removing all nodes tree on CHILD_NODES_LIST eviction - do not guarantee cache consistence.
Lets see the usecase.

we have such nodes
/node1[3]/child1/child2/child3

Cache do not have full nodes tree (those nodes was added many time ago, and info about those nodes already removed by eviction).
Than:
- node1[3] and child3 nodes are added to cache again;
- node1[3] is reordered;

There is no chains between node1[3] and child3, so updateTreePath can not find and update child3.

So, there is two possible decision:
- clean cache on sibling reordering;
- check all items in cache - is it descendant of reordered node?.

Second one is no so bad, as it seemed at first glance:
- iteration is hard operation, but it will be executed only on samename siblings;
- there is no additional operations on eviction;
- we do not need to bother about links to child;

