Currently we cannot return Collection<T> directly response. For example : 

{code}
Collection<Foo> coll = ....;
...
return Response.ok(coll, MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON).cacheControl(cacheControl).build();
{code}
this does not work because we need to return a bean directly. So what is commonly done by developers is wrapping the collection in a bean. For example : 

{code}
return Response.ok(new CollectionWrapper(coll), MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON).cacheControl(cacheControl).build();
{code}
with CollectionWrapper looking something like : 

{code}
public class CollectionWrapper<T> {
  private Collection<T> jsonList;

  public CollectionWrapper(Collection<T> list) {
    this.jsonList = list;
  }

 // getters and setters not shown
...
}
{code}


This plumbing class is an unnecessary hassle for the developer. Please improve by allowing to return directly a Collection in response.

